OL,3,CCouncil 'learning lessons' after
OL,4,Cpupils left confused over grammar
OL,5,Cschool test
OL,7,FThe council added that they don't
OL,8,Fadvise that pupils need to be tutored
OL,9,Ffor the test, and that it was
OL,10,Fspecifically designed to 'last for the
OL,11,Ftime that was given, and so it was an
OL,12,Fappropriate amount of time for the
OL,13,Fquestions that were asked.'
OL,15,FCllr Coombs added: :We're absolutely
OL,16,Flearning a lesson from this.
OL,18,F"We don't want parents to feel
OL,19,Fstressed or children and so we'll be
OL,20,Flooking closely at how we communicate
OL,21,Fnext year.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/5
